== Noun ==


The initial smell of water (rain) on rock - or pavements -  on a warm day. This (usually pleasant) smell is caused by evaporation of oils from the surface. 

== Etymology ==

The word, coined by  geologists, first came into use in the 1960's .

Literally meaning rock-essence from 'Petros'(Rock) and 'ichor'(The blood in the veins of Greek Gods).